1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. dxe5 dxe5 5. Qxd8+ Kxd8 6. f4 Bb4 7. Bd3 exf4 8. Bxf4 Be6 9. Nge2 Nbd7 10. O-O-O Bd6 11. Bb5 Bxf4+ 12. Nxf4 c6 13. Nxe6+ $2 {A typical mistake. White is worse statically. He should be looking for a concrete solution instead.} ({Stronger was} 13. e5 Ng4 14. Nxe6+ fxe6 15. Bc4 Ke7 16. Rd6 Nf8 17. Re1 $1 {with the tactical point} Nxe5 18. Rxe6+ $1 Nxe6 19. Rxe5 $18) 13... fxe6 14. Be2 Ke7 15. Kd2 Ne5 {[%csl Be5,Re2][%cal Ge5f3,Ge5d3,Ge5c4,Ge5g4] Dark-squared strategy. Perfect knight. Outpost that all the black pieces can use.} 16. h3 g5 $1 17. Ke3 h5 $1 {[%csl Gh4,Rg3,Rf4,Yg2][%cal Gh5h4,Ge5g6,Gf6d7,Gd7e5,Gg6f4]} 18. g3 h4 $1 {[%csl Re2,Re4,Rh3] Fixing another weakness.} 19. Rhg1 Rag8 20. gxh4 $2 Rxh4 21. Rg3 Nf7 22. Rd4 Rgh8 23. Bf1 (23. Bg4 Ne5 $19) 23... Nh5 24. Rg1 Nf4 $19 25. Ra4 Nxh3 26. Rg3 a6 27. Ra3 Nf4 28. Rb3 b5 29. a4 Rh1 30. Bd3 R8h3 31. Rxh3 Rxh3+ 32. Kd4 g4 33. axb5 axb5 34. Ra3 g3 35. Ra7+ Kf8 36. Bf1 Rh8 37. Ra1 {0-1 Black wins.} 0-1

