1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. dxe5 (4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. Bc4 Be7 6. O-O O-O) 4... dxe5 5. Qxd8+ Kxd8 6. Nf3 (6. Bg5 Be6 7. O-O-O+ Nbd7 8. Nf3 Bd6 (8... Kc8 $5)) (6. Bc4 Be6 (6... Ke8 $5) 7. Bxe6 fxe6) 6... Bd6 7. Bg5 Be6 8. O-O-O Nbd7 9. Nb5 $6 Ke7 10. Nxd6 cxd6 {Carlsen also liked the position from Black's side and gave the following instructive game} 11. Bb5 (11. Nd2 h6 12. Bh4 g5 13. Bg3 Rac8) 11... Rhd8 (11... Nc5 12. Rhe1 a6 13. Bf1 Rac8 14. Kb1 b5 15. Nd2 h6 16. Bxf6+ Kxf6 {Black is actually better here.}) 12. Nd2 h6 13. Bh4 g5 14. Bg3 a6 15. Bxd7 (15. Be2 Rac8 (15... d5) 16. f3 Nh5) 15... Rxd7 $15 {[%csl Ge6,Rg3][%cal Ge6h3,Ge6a2] The difference in the activity of the bishops is striking.} 16. f3 Rc8 17. Kb1 Nh5 18. Nf1 (18. Bf2 Nf4 19. g3 Nh3 20. Be3 (20. Bb6 Rc6 21. Be3 f5) 20... f5) 18... f5 19. exf5 Bxf5 20. Ne3 Bg6 21. Rd2 Ke6 22. b3 b5 23. Kb2 d5 24. Re1 Nxg3 25. hxg3 h5 26. c3 d4 27. cxd4 Rxd4 28. Rxd4 exd4 29. Nc2+ (29. Nc4+ Kf6 (29... Kd5 $4 30. Nb6+)) 29... Kd5 30. Nb4+ Kd6 31. Rc1 $2 (31. Nxa6 Rc2+ 32. Ka3 Rxg2) 31... Rxc1 32. Kxc1 h4 $1 {[%csl Rg2][%cal Rg1g2]} 33. gxh4 gxh4 34. Nxa6 (34. Kd2 a5 (34... Ke5 35. Ke2 Kf4 36. Kf2 a5 37. Nd5+ Ke5 38. Ne7 Be8) 35. Nc2 (35. Nd3 Bxd3 36. Kxd3 Ke5 $19) 35... Bxc2 36. Kxc2 Ke5 37. Kd3 Kf4 38. Kxd4 Kg3 $19) 34... Bd3 35. Nb4 Bf1 36. Kd2 Bxg2 37. Ke2 Bh3 38. a4 (38. Nd3 Bf5 39. Nf2 b4 40. f4 h3 41. Kf3 Kd5 42. Nd1 Bb1 $19) 38... Bf5 39. axb5 d3+ 40. Ke3 h3 41. Nxd3 Bxd3 42. Kd4 {0-1 Black wins} 0-1

