1. d4 d6 2. e4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. dxe5 dxe5 5. Qxd8+ Kxd8 6. Bc4 Be6 7. Bxe6 fxe6 8. f3 { You have already noticed that Gagunashvili is one of the best players on the black side of the Philidor. Which means that he knows stuff... It is time to look at White's best try in the endgame. It consists in arranging the knights on the best possible squares in order to aim the e5-pawn. } 8... a6 9. Be3 Bd6 $6 { As we shall see, Black can fight the plan immediately. } 10. O-O-O Ke7 11. Nh3 $1 ( 11. Nge2 Nh5 $5 { [%csl Rf4,Rg3][%cal Rh5f4,Rh5g3] } ) ( 11. h4 Nh5 { [%cal Gh5f4,Gh5g3] } ) 11... Nbd7 12. Nf2 Bc5 { One of the seemingly good ideas. } ( { The other way to fight is } 12... Raf8 $5 { [%cal Gf6h5,Gh5f4]  Nh5 } ) 13. Bxc5+ Nxc5 14. h4 $14 { [%csl Gg4][%cal Gg2g5,Gf2g4,Gd1d2,Gb7b5,Ga6a5,Gb5b4,Ga5a4,Gb2b4,Gg4g5,Gh4h5] It transpires that the white knights are stronger and more stable than the opponent's ones. } ( 14. Nd3 ) ( 14. b4 ) 14... Rad8 ( 14... h5 { g5 } ) ( 14... Nh5 15. Ng4 Nd7 16. Rd2 $14 ) 15. h5 h6 ( { Still, Black might be able to defend after } 15... Rxd1+ 16. Kxd1 Rd8+ 17. Ke2 $14 ) 16. b4 Rxd1+ ( 16... Ncd7 17. Nd3 $14 ) 17. Kxd1 Ncd7 ( 17... Rd8+ 18. Ke2 Ncd7 19. Nd3 $14 ) 18. Nd3 { [%csl Gb4] } 18... Kd6 { [ c5] } ( 18... a5 $13 { was a must, looking for immediate counterplay. } ) 19. Na4 b6 ( 19... b5 20. Nab2 ( 20. Nac5 Nxc5 21. Nxc5 ( 21. bxc5+ Kc6 ) 21... Nd7 22. Nxd7 ( 22. Nxa6 Ra8 ) ( 22. Nb7+ Kc6 23. Na5+ Kb6 { c5 } ) 22... Kxd7 ) 20... c5 21. c4 cxb4 22. cxb5 a5 ( 22... axb5 23. Nxb4 $14 ) 23. Nc4+ Kc7 24. Ke2 $16 ) 20. Ke2 Rb8 ( 20... c5 21. Nxb6 ) 21. Nab2 $1 { [%csl Bd3][%cal Bb2c4,Bd3e5,Bc4e5] That is the type of set-up White is aiming for. The knights cannot be stopped. } ( 21. Rd1 Ke7 ( 21... Nxh5 22. Ndc5+ ) 22. g4 $14 ) 21... b5 22. c4 c5 23. g4 a5 ( 23... cxb4 24. Nxb4 $16 ) 24. bxc5+ ( 24. Rd1 Kc6 ( 24... Ke7 25. bxc5 $18 ) ( 24... Kc7 25. bxc5 b4 26. Na4 $16 ) 25. a4 $18 { Gurevich,M } ) 24... Nxc5 25. cxb5 Nxd3 ( 25... Rxb5 26. Nc4+ ) 26. Kxd3 Rxb5 27. Nc4+ Ke7 ( 27... Kc7 28. Rc1 $18 ) 28. Rh2 $1 { [ Rb2] } 28... Nd7 29. Rb2 Nc5+ ( 29... Rxb2 30. Nxb2 ) 30. Kc2 Rxb2+ 31. Kxb2 Nd3+ ( 31... Kf6 32. Nxa5 Kg5 33. Nb3 { Nd2 } ) 32. Kc3 Ne1 ( 32... Nb4 33. Kb3 Nd3 ( 33... Nc6 34. Ka4 ) 34. Ka4 ) 33. Nxe5 { [NB 2/e] } 33... Kd6 34. f4 Ng2 35. Nd3 ( 35. Nc4+ Kc5 36. f5 $18 ) 35... Ne3 36. g5 Nf1 37. f5 $1 exf5 ( 37... hxg5 38. f6 $18 ) ( 37... Ng3 38. e5+ Ke7 39. f6+ $18 ) ( 37... Ke7 38. f6+ gxf6 39. gxh6 Kf7 40. Nf4 $18 ) 38. exf5 Ke7 ( 38... hxg5 39. f6 $18 ) ( 38... Ng3 39. f6 $18 ) 39. f6+ gxf6 ( 39... Kf7 40. Ne5+ $18 ) ( 39... Kf8 40. g6 $1 gxf6 41. Nf4 $18 ) 40. gxh6 Kf7 41. Kc4 { 1-0 White wins. } 1-0
