1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. dxe5 dxe5 5. Qxd8+ Kxd8 6. Bc4 Be6 7. Bxe6 fxe6 { The pair of knights might not always be favorable for White as the following game shows } 8. Be3 Bb4 $1 { An important move, that intends to disrupt White's plans. } 9. O-O-O+ { The castling is already a concession as White will find it hard to maneuver her knights to the optimal squares. } ( 9. Bd2 Nbd7 ( 9... Ke7 $5 10. f3 c5 ) 10. f3 a6 11. Nh3 Ke7 12. Nf2 Bd6 13. a4 b6 14. Ke2 c5 15. Rhb1 Nb8 $1 16. Ncd1 Nc6 17. c3 c4 18. b4 cxb3 19. Rxb3 Nd7 20. Bg5+ Kf7 $13 21. Ne3 Na5 22. Rb2 Be7 23. Rd1 Ra7 24. Bxe7 Kxe7 25. Nd3 Rc8 26. Rc1 Rac7 27. Kd2 Rc6 28. Rbb1 Rd6 29. Ke2 Nc4 30. Nxc4 Rxc4 31. Rb4 Rc7 32. Rbb1 Nc5 33. Nxc5 Rxc5 34. Rb4 a5 35. Rb3 Rc4 36. Ra3 Rdc6 { 1/2-1/2 (36) Martic,I (2352) -Warakomski,T (2537) Heraklion 2018 } ) 9... Ke7 10. Nge2 Nbd7 11. f3 c6 12. Nb1 b5 13. c3 Bd6 ( 13... Bc5 $5 ) 14. g4 Rhf8 15. Nd2 a5 16. Ng3 Bc5 17. Bxc5+ Nxc5 $15 { [%cal Gc5d3,Gd3f2] The black knights are far more active as in the previous case, she is in control. } 18. Kc2 a4 19. h4 Rad8 20. g5 Nfd7 21. Rdf1 Nb6 22. Rh2 Nd3 $17 23. Nh1 Rf4 ( 23... Nc4 $3 24. Nxc4 bxc4 $19 ) 24. Nf2 Nxf2 ( 24... Nxb2 $19 ) 25. Rfxf2 Rdf8 26. Kd3 h5 ( 26... Rd8+ 27. Kc2 c5 $15 ) 27. gxh6 gxh6 28. Ke2 Rg8 29. Nf1 Nc4 30. b3 axb3 31. axb3 Na5 32. Nd2 Nb7 33. h5 Nc5 34. Rf1 Rg5 35. Ra1 Rf7 36. Ra8 Kf6 37. Rc8 Ra7 38. Rxc6 Nd7 39. Rd6 Ke7 40. Rc6 Ra2 41. Ke3 Rg1 42. c4 bxc4 43. Rxc4 Re1+ 44. Re2 Rh1 45. Rc7 Rxh5 46. Nc4 Rxe2+ 47. Kxe2 Rh2+ 48. Ke3 Kd8 49. Ra7 h5 50. b4 h4 51. b5 h3 52. b6 Nxb6 53. Nxb6 Rb2 54. Nc4 h2 55. Rh7 Rc2 56. Nxe5 Ke8 57. Ng4 { 1-0 White wins. } 1-0
