1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. dxe5 dxe5 5. Qxd8+ Kxd8 6. Bg5 Be6 7. O-O-O+ Nd7 { The direct attacking tries do not lead White anywhere. } 8. f4 { [%cal Gf4f5] } 8... exf4 9. Nf3 ( { Or } 9. e5 h6 10. Bh4 g5 11. exf6 gxh4 { [%cal Gf8c5,Gc5e3] } ) 9... h6 ( 9... Bc5 { [%cal Gc5e3] } 10. e5 h6 11. exf6 hxg5 12. fxg7 Rg8 13. Nxg5 Rxg7 14. Nxe6+ fxe6 15. g3 f3 16. Rd3 f2 17. Ne4 Bb6 18. Rf3 Ke7 { superior opposite-colored bishop in Sprenger,J (2490) -Bojkov,D (2446) Bad Godesberg 2004 } ) ( { From theoretical perspective, easier equality is achieved with } 9... Kc8 10. Bxf4 Bc5 11. h3 ( 11. e5 Ng4 12. Ne4 Be3+ 13. Bxe3 Nxe3 14. Re1 Nxf1 15. Rhxf1 Kd8 ( 15... Re8 $10 ) 16. Nd4 Ke7 17. b3 h6 ) 11... Nh5 12. Bh2 Be3+ 13. Kb1 Bf4 14. Bxf4 ( 14. g4 Bxh2 15. Rxh2 Nf4 16. Rf2 Ng6 17. Nd4 Nge5 18. Nd5 c6 19. Bg2 Re8 ) 14... Nxf4 15. Nd5 Ng6 16. Bc4 c6 17. Ne3 Kc7 18. Bxe6 fxe6 19. Rhf1 Rae8 20. Ng4 Rhf8 21. Kc1 h6 { 1/2-1/2 (21) Efimenko,Z (2654) -Golod,V (2602) Ohrid 2009 } ) 10. Bxf4 Ng4 $2 { Wrong plan. Black is not prepared to play aggressively. However, there are many other good options: } ( 10... c6 11. a3 Ng4 12. Bg3 Bc5 13. Nd4 Bxd4 14. Rxd4 f6 15. Bd6 Nge5 16. Ne2 Ke8 17. Nf4 Kf7 18. Be2 Rhe8 19. Rhd1 Kg8 20. a4 Bf7 21. Ba3 Nf8 22. a5 b6 23. b3 Ne6 24. Nxe6 Bxe6 25. Bd6 Nf7 26. Bg3 b5 27. h3 a6 28. Bd6 Rac8 29. Bc5 Ne5 30. Kb2 Bf7 31. Rd6 Bg6 32. Bf3 Bf7 33. Kc3 Be6 34. Bh5 Bf7 35. Be2 Bg6 36. Bf3 Bf7 37. R1d2 Be6 38. Be2 Bf7 39. Kb2 Bg6 40. Bf3 Bf7 41. Rd1 Be6 42. Bh5 Bf7 43. Bxf7+ Kxf7 44. Bd4 Rc7 45. Bxe5 Rxe5 46. Rd7+ Rxd7 47. Rxd7+ Re7 48. Rd8 Re8 49. Rd7+ Re7 50. Rd4 c5 51. Rd6 Re6 52. Rb6 h5 53. Kc3 g5 54. Kd3 Ke7 55. Rb7+ Kd6 56. Ra7 Ke5 57. Ke3 h4 58. Rf7 b4 59. Rd7 Rd6 60. Rc7 Rd1 61. Rxc5+ Ke6 62. Rc6+ Ke5 63. Rxa6 Re1+ 64. Kf3 Rf1+ 65. Ke2 Rg1 66. Kf2 Rc1 67. Rc6 Kxe4 68. a6 Kd5 69. Rc4 Ra1 70. Rxb4 Rxa6 71. Kf3 Ra1 72. Rb6 Rf1+ 73. Ke3 Re1+ 74. Kf3 Rf1+ 75. Ke3 Re1+ 76. Kf2 Rc1 77. c4+ Ke5 78. Rc6 Rc2+ 79. Kg1 Rb2 80. Rb6 f5 81. c5 g4 82. hxg4 fxg4 83. Rb4 g3 84. Kf1 Rb1+ 85. Ke2 h3 { 0-1 (85) Vera Siguenas,D (2503) -Almeida Quintana,O (2521) Havana 2018 } ) ( 10... Bc5 $11 ) ( 10... Kc8 $11 ) 11. Bg3 Ne3 12. Rd3 Nxf1 13. Rxf1 Kc8 $4 { A blunder, but Black's position is already very bad. } 14. Rfd1 ( 14. Nb5 $1 Bc4 15. Nxc7 Bxd3 16. cxd3 Rb8 17. Nd4 $18 ) 14... Be7 15. Nb5 Nc5 16. Nxc7 Nxd3+ 17. Rxd3 Rb8 18. Nxe6 fxe6 19. Bxb8 Kxb8 20. Ne5 $18 Re8 21. Kd1 Bf6 22. Nd7+ Kc7 23. Nxf6 gxf6 24. Rh3 Rh8 25. Ke2 Kd6 26. Rh5 Ke7 27. Rb5 b6 28. a4 Rc8 29. Kd3 e5 30. a5 Rc6 31. c4 h5 32. b4 h4 33. c5 bxa5 34. Rxa5 Rc7 35. Kc4 Kd8 36. Ra6 Rg7 37. b5 Rxg2 38. Rxa7 Rxh2 39. b6 h3 40. Rh7 Rc2+ 41. Kd5 h2 42. b7 { 1-0 White wins. } 1-0
