1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. Bc4 Be7 6. O-O Nb6 7. Qd3 exd4 ( { The easiest way to equalize is } 7... Nxc4 $1 8. Qxc4 exd4 9. Nxd4 O-O 10. Re1 Re8 11. Bf4 { when Black should be looking for a timely d6-d5 break, as in the line } 11... c5 ( 11... Bd7 ) 12. Nde2 a6 13. a4 Be6 14. Qd3 d5 $15 ) 8. Nxd4 O-O 9. Bb3 Nfd7 10. Bf4 Nc5 11. Qf3 Bf6 12. Rad1 Bd7 13. Rfe1 Re8 14. Bg3 Nxb3 ( 14... a5 $5 15. a3 Nxb3 16. cxb3 ( 16. Nxb3 $6 Nc4 ) 16... a4 17. b4 Nc4 $13 ) 15. axb3 Qe7 16. Re3 Be5 17. Qe2 Qf6 18. Ndb5 Bxg3 19. hxg3 Qd8 20. Nd4 a6 21. Qd2 Qf6 $10 22. Rde1 Rad8 23. Nf3 Be6 24. Rd3 Nd7 25. Qf4 Qxf4 ( 25... h6 $5 ) 26. gxf4 Nb6 { Too passive. } ( { Better was to open the diagonal for the bishop with } 26... f5 $1 27. Ng5 ( 27. Nd4 fxe4 28. Rxe4 Bf7 $10 ) 27... fxe4 28. Ngxe4 h6 ) 27. f5 Bd7 28. g4 $14 { White's endgame is preferable. Is he winning is a different story. } 28... h6 29. Kg2 f6 30. Kg3 Re7 31. Rde3 Rde8 32. Nh4 Bc6 33. Ng6 Rd7 34. f4 Rdd8 35. e5 dxe5 36. fxe5 fxe5 37. Rxe5 Rxe5 38. Rxe5 Nc8 39. Re2 Rd4 40. Nf4 Kf7 41. Ne6 Rd7 42. Na2 Ne7 ( 42... Rd1 $1 43. Nb4 Rg1+ $13 ) 43. Nb4 Bb5 44. c4 a5 45. Nc2 Bc6 46. Ncd4 b6 47. Kf4 Kf6 48. Ke3 Bb7 49. Rh2 c5 50. Ne2 Nc6 51. N2f4 Ne5 52. Nh5+ Kf7 53. Kf4 Nd3+ 54. Kg3 g6 55. Nhf4 gxf5 56. Rxh6 Nxf4 57. Nxf4 fxg4 58. Kxg4 Be4 59. Rxb6 Rd2 60. Ne6 Bc2 61. Nxc5 Bd1+ 62. Kf5 Rf2+ 63. Ke5 Rxb2 64. Rb5 Ra2 65. Kd6 Ra1 66. Kc6 Rc1 67. Kd5 Ra1 68. Rb6 Rb1 69. Ra6 Bxb3 70. Nxb3 Rxb3 71. Rxa5 Ke7 72. Kc6 Rc3 73. c5 Kd8 74. Ra8+ Ke7 75. Rc8 Rh3 76. Kc7 Ke6 77. Rd8 { 1-0 White wins. } 1-0
