{ [#] Space issues. Many pieces. } 20. Bc4 { [%csl Rc7][%cal Gg3b8] The most common problem in the Philidor middlegame is the lack of space for the second player. If all the pieces remain on the board, White's superior coordination might lead to immediate problems, as in the next three examples. } ( { White missed a good chance for a decisive breakthrough with } 20. e5 $1 dxe5 ( 20... Nd7 21. exd6 Bxd6 22. Rxe8+ Rxe8 { [%csl Rc7,Rd6] } 23. Ndb5 $1 cxb5 24. Nxb5 Qxc2 25. Nxd6 $18 ) ( 20... Nh7 21. exd6 Bxd6 22. Rxe8+ Rxe8 23. Ndb5 $1 ) ( 20... Nd5 { [%cal Gd4b5] } 21. Nxd5 cxd5 22. Bb5 Bd7 23. e6 $1 fxe6 24. Bxd7 Qxd7 25. Rxe6 Rxe6 26. Qxd5 $18 { [%cal Gf4f5,Gd5g8] } ) 21. fxe5 Nxe5 22. Rxe5 Rxe5 23. Bxe5 Qxe5 24. Nxc6 $1 { [%csl Rd8,Re5][%cal Gd1d8,Rc6e5,Rc6d8] } 24... bxc6 25. Rxd8 $18 ) 20... Qb6 21. Bb3 Qc5 22. f5 Ne5 { [%csl Ge5,Gf6,Gc5] } 23. Qf1 Qb6 24. Nf3 Qc7 25. Bh4 Nxf3 26. gxf3 Be7 27. Qg2 Nh7 28. Rg1 Bf8 29. f6 g5 30. f4 Qd7 31. Rd3 Kh8 32. fxg5 hxg5 33. Bxg5 { 1-0 White wins. } 1-0
