{ Ng1! [#]Here too, all the pieces are on the board, therefore, White is significantly better and ready to break through } 22. Kh1 { [%cal Be4e5,Bg1h1] Too timid. } ( 22. e5 $1 { would have led to a decisive advantage, for example } 22... dxe5 ( 22... Nfd7 23. exd6 Rxe1+ 24. Qxe1 Bxd6 25. Ndb5 cxb5 26. Nxb5 Qb8 27. Rxd6 Rxd6 28. Qe8+ Nf8 29. Be5 Rd1+ 30. Kh2 Qa8 31. Nd6 $18 ) 23. fxe5 Nfd7 24. e6 $1 Nxe6 25. Nxe6 Rxe6 26. Rxe6 fxe6 27. Ne4 { [%csl Rd7,Rf6,Ra6,Rc8][%cal Rb2h8,Re4f6,Rd1d7] with decisive attack. } ) 22... Bg7 23. Ba3 Nfd7 24. Qd2 Qd8 25. Nde2 Qh4 { 1/2-1/2 The game is a draw. Even in the final positon, White is significantly better after the maneuver Ne2-g1-f3! } 1/2-1/2
