{[#]Not all the positions with all the pieces on the board are superior for the first player. Black can also achieve proper co-ordination and exploit different tactical possibilities in order to fix other positional advantages, such as full control over the dark squares. Just as Dubov did in the following game} 21... h4 $1 ({But not} 21... Nh7 {[%cal Gf6d7]} 22. f4 Nf8 23. f5 {[%cal Gf5f6] when White gets what he wants}) 22. Bxh4 Nh5 $36 {[%csl Rh4][%cal Rh4g3,Rh5g3,Gg7e5,Ge5h2]} 23. Nce2 ({Alas, there is no} 23. f4 $2 Nxf4 $1 {[%cal Gg7e5,Ge5h2]}) 23... d5 $1 {[%csl Ge8,Gd8][%cal Gb6d4,Gg7d4,Gh5f4,Gc8h3,Ge8e1,Gd8d1,Gd4f2] It suddenly transpires that it is Black who has the better coordination.} 24. exd5 Rxd5 25. f4 Rdd8 26. Nf3 Rxd1 27. Rxd1 Qc7 28. Nfg1 Ne4 $17 {0-1 (41) Carlsen,M (2863) -Dubov,D (2699) chess24.com INT 2020} 0-1

