1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 Nf6 4. Nc3 Nbd7 { [%csl Gd7][%cal Gd7e5,Gd6e5] Hinders the development, but supports the center. } 5. Bc4 Be7 6. O-O O-O 7. Qe2 { [%cal Gf1d1] } 7... c6 { Black is building a better center, but White owes the initiative. } 8. a4 Qc7 9. Bb3 a6 10. h3 exd4 { Giving up the center. } 11. Nxd4 Re8 { [%cal Ge8e4,Gf6e4] } 12. Bf4 Bf8 { [%cal Ge8e4,Gf6e4] } 13. f3 Nc5 $1 { [%csl Gc5][%cal Rc5b3] . } ( 13... Ne5 { but Black wants to trade first to fight the deficit of space. } ) 14. Ba2 Ne6 $1 { [%csl Gd4,Gf4] Trading a pair of pieces. } 15. Bxe6 Bxe6 { [%cal Gc8e6,Ga8d8,Ge6c8] } 16. Qd2 Rad8 17. Rfe1 Bc8 18. Rad1 Nd7 $1 { Now Black can occupy the outpost after harmoniously developing his pieces. } 19. Nf5 Ne5 $15 { The knight is dominating in the center. If White wants to expel it he would weaken the e4 pawn. } 20. Nd4 f6 { [%csl Re4] Fixes the e4 pawn. } 21. Kh1 Qf7 ( 21... b5 $1 { D. B. } ) 22. Qf2 Qg6 23. b3 { [%csl Ge5] } 23... Nf7 { Prepares f6-f5. The knight on e5 did not do much but did not allow White to do anything. } ( 23... d5 $5 24. exd5 Bb4 { [%cal Gb4e1] } 25. Re3 cxd5 $13 ) 24. Kh2 Re7 25. Nde2 f5 $1 { [%csl Ra4,Rb3,Rc2][%cal Rc2a4] Demolition of the paralyzed e4-pawn. } 26. Ng3 fxe4 $2 { Too hasty. } ( 26... Rde8 { first, for example } 27. exf5 Bxf5 28. Nxf5 Qxf5 29. Bg3 Rxe1 30. Rxe1 Rxe1 31. Qxe1 Qxc2 { . } ) 27. Ncxe4 ( 27. fxe4 { the isolani would be weak. } ) 27... d5 28. Nc5 Rde8 29. Nd3 Rxe1 { Black only got equal game. } ( 29... Nd6 30. Be5 { ) . } ) 30. Rxe1 Rxe1 31. Qxe1 Qe6 32. Qxe6 Bxe6 33. Be3 Bd6 34. f4 Kf8 35. Kg1 g6 36. Kf2 h5 37. Nc5 Bc8 38. a5 Nh6 39. b4 Kf7 40. c3 Ng8 ( 40... Nf5 ) 41. Kf3 Nf6 42. Bd4 Bxc5 43. Bxc5 Be6 44. Bd4 Ne4 45. Ne2 $1 ( 45. Nxe4 dxe4+ 46. Kxe4 Bd5+ ) 45... Bf5 46. g4 hxg4+ 47. hxg4 Nd2+ ( 47... Bd7 { ) } ) 48. Kg3 Bc2 49. Ng1 Ke6 50. Kh4 Bd1 51. Nh3 Ne4 52. f5+ $1 gxf5 $2 ( 52... Kf7 53. fxg6+ Kxg6 54. Nf4+ $16 ) 53. Nf4+ Kf7 54. g5 $1 Bg4 55. g6+ Ke7 56. g7 Kf7 57. Ng6 { 1-0 White wins. } 1-0
