{Model play for Black. [#] Therefore, one of the key ideas for the second player in the Philidor is to swap off a pair of light pieces.} 14. Nf5 $2 {[%cal Bf2f3,Bd4f5]} (14. f3 $1) 14... Nc5 $1 {[%csl Ge4][%cal Gc5e4,Gc8f5] [#]} (14... Nxe4 15. Nxe4 Rxe4 16. Bf4 {[%cal Gf4d6,Gf5d6,Gd2d6]} Rxe1+ 17. Rxe1) 15. Bxc5 (15. f3 Bxf5 16. exf5 {[%csl Rf5,Rf3,Rg2,Rh3]} d5 {[%csl Ra2,Gb7,Gc6,Gd5]}) 15... dxc5 16. Rad1 $2 {[%cal Ga2f7]} Bxf5 $1 17. exf5 Rad8 {Black has enough room to maneuver with his remaining pieces and is already better.} 18. Qc1 Rxe1+ $1 19. Rxe1 Rd4 $1 20. Qe3 Qd7 $17 21. Qf3 Rd2 22. Nb1 Rd4 23. Nc3 Rb4 (23... b5 $5 {[%csl Ra2][%cal Gc5c4,Rb5b4]}) (23... c4 $19 {[%cal Gb7b5]}) 24. Rd1 Qe7 25. b3 Rd4 26. Bb1 Qe5 27. Rf1 c4 28. Qe3 Qxe3 29. fxe3 Rd8 30. bxc4 Bc5 31. Re1 Bb4 32. Rd1 Re8 33. Rd3 Bxc3 34. Rxc3 Ne4 35. Ra3 Nc5 36. Kf2 Re4 37. Ba2 Kf8 38. Bb3 Re8 39. Ra1 Rd8 40. Kf3 Ke7 41. g4 Rd2 42. Rf1 f6 43. Kf4 Nd7 44. e4 Ne5 45. c5 Nd7 46. Ke3 Rh2 47. Kd4 Ne5 48. Rb1 Kd8 49. Be6 Kc7 50. Rb3 Rxc2 51. Rg3 Rh2 52. Rb3 Rd2+ 53. Ke3 Rd1 54. Rc3 Ra1 55. Bb3 Rf1 56. Ke2 Rh1 57. Kf2 Rh2+ 58. Kg3 Rd2 59. Bc2 Re2 60. Kf4 Rf2+ 61. Ke3 Rf3+ 62. Kd4 Rxc3 63. Kxc3 b6 64. cxb6+ Kxb6 65. Bd1 Kc5 66. Be2 Nd7 67. Bd3 Kd6 68. Kd4 Nb6 69. e5+ fxe5+ 70. Ke4 Nxa4 71. Bc4 Nb6 72. Ba2 Nd5 73. Bc4 a4 74. h4 a3 75. g5 hxg5 76. hxg5 a2 77. Bxa2 Nc3+ {0-1 Black wins.} 0-1

