1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. Bc4 Be7 6. O-O O-O 7. a4 c6 8. Re1 b6 9. Ba2 a6 { [%cal Gc8h3] } 10. h3 { Another waiting useful move. } 10... Bb7 { [%csl Yb7][%cal Rc8d7,Yc8b7] Now that the bishop is no longer defending the knight, White can finally maneuver the knight. } 11. dxe5 ( 11. Nh4 exd4 ( 11... Nxe4 12. Nxe4 Bxh4 13. Nxd6 Bxf2+ 14. Kxf2 Qf6+ 15. Kg1 Qxd6 16. dxe5 Qxd1 17. Rxd1 Nxe5 18. Bf4 { Power bishops. } 18... Rae8 ( 18... Ng6 19. Be3 b5 $16 { would have been more resilient. } ) 19. Re1 Ng6 20. Bd6 Bc8 ( 20... Rxe1+ 21. Rxe1 Rd8 ( 21... Rc8 22. Rf1 ( 22. b4 $5 ) 22... Nh8 23. b4 { with complete domination for White. } ) 22. Bc7 Rc8 23. Bxb6 ) 21. a5 b5 22. Bxf8 Rxe1+ 23. Rxe1 Kxf8 24. c4 { 1-0 Smirin, I (2637) -Cherniaev,A (2431) /Biel SUI 2008/The Week in Chess 717 } ) 12. Qxd4 d5 13. exd5 Nxd5 14. Nxd5 Bxh4 ( 14... cxd5 15. Nf5 Bf6 16. Qg4 Ne5 17. Qg3 $14 ) 15. Nc3 Bf6 16. Qd6 Nc5 17. Bf4 Qc8 ( 17... Bxc3 18. bxc3 Nxa4 19. Re7 { [%csl Ga2,Gf4] } 19... Qxd6 20. Bxd6 Rad8 21. Bc7 Ra8 22. Be5 Bc8 23. Bd6 Bf5 24. Rc7 $16 ) ( 17... Re8 18. Qxd8 Raxd8 19. Bc7 Bxc3 20. bxc3 Rc8 21. Bxb6 Nxa4 22. Rxe8+ Rxe8 23. Bd4 c5 24. Bb3 cxd4 25. Bxa4 Rc8 ( 25... Rd8 26. Rd1 $16 ) 26. cxd4 Rc4 27. c3 Rxc3 $14 28. Rb1 Rc7 29. d5 $18 ) 18. a5 $16 { Kozakov-V. Georgiev,Croatia 2003. } ) 11... dxe5 ( { From theoretical point, a good defense is } 11... Nxe5 $1 { [%cal Gf3h4,Gf3d4] } 12. Nh4 ( 12. Nd4 ) 12... Re8 13. Nf5 Bf8 $11 { [%csl Rf5][%cal Rg7g6] } ) 12. Nh4 b5 13. Nf5 Bc5 14. Qf3 Bd4 ( 14... b4 15. Ne2 Kh8 16. Be3 $16 ) 15. Bh6 $18 g6 ( 15... Ne8 16. Qg3 Qf6 17. Bg5 $18 { [%csl Rf6][%cal Rf6g6,Rf5e7] } ) 16. Rad1 gxf5 17. Qg3+ Ng4 18. hxg4 f4 19. Qh3 Qe7 20. Ne2 Bb6 21. Qh5 Nc5 22. Bg5 Qc7 23. Bf6 Nxe4 24. Nd4 Qd6 25. Bxe5 { 1-0 Bojkov,D (2521) -Molina,F (2245) /Bergamo 2009 } 1-0
