1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. Bc4 Be7 6. O-O O-O 7. h3 c6 8. a4 a5 9. Re1 h6 10. Ba2 exd4 11. Nxd4 { This game can also demonstrate The idea of locking the bishop on a2. } 11... Nc5 { [%cal Gd1f3] } 12. Qf3 Be6 { [%csl Ra2,Rf3][%cal Ga2e6,Gf7e6,Gf8f2] } 13. Nf5 Nh7 14. Qg3 Bxf5 $1 15. Bxh6 Bg5 $2 ( { Missing the correct idea } 15... Ng5 $1 { [%csl Rh6] } 16. Bxg5 Bxg5 17. exf5 Qf6 $1 { [%csl Ra1,Ra2][%cal Gc5e4,Ge1e4,Gd6d5,Gf6b2] with inevitable d6-d5. Once it is played, Black will practically have an extra piece on the opposite side of the board. } ( { But not yet } 17... d5 18. Rad1 Qf6 19. Qc7 $13 ) 18. Rad1 { [%csl Gd5,Gc7][%cal Gd6d5,Gg3c7] } 18... Rae8 19. Rxe8 Rxe8 20. Rxd6 Re1+ 21. Kh2 Qxf5 { [%csl Gg5,Gf5,Gc5,Rc3,Ra2][%cal Gg5f4,Gf4h2,Gf4d6,Rc4c3,Gg5d8,Gf5c8,Gf5f7] } ) ( 15... Bg6 $4 16. Qxg6 { [%cal Ga2g8] } ) 16. Bxg5 Qxg5 17. Qxg5 Nxg5 18. exf5 d5 { Alas, the bishop will not be locked on the queenside for long. } 19. h4 Nh7 20. g4 Rfe8 21. f3 Nf6 22. Rxe8+ Rxe8 23. Rd1 Nfd7 24. Kf2 Kf8 25. b3 $1 Na6 26. Ne2 $1 Nf6 27. c3 $1 { [%cal Ga2b1,Gb1f5,Gg4g5] } 27... Nc7 28. Bb1 c5 29. Bd3 Rd8 30. h5 Ke7 31. Nf4 d4 32. c4 Rh8 33. Be4 b6 34. g5 Nfe8 35. Rg1 Kd6 36. Rh1 Ke5 37. Nd3+ Kd6 { 1-0 White wins. } 1-0
