{[#] Space advantage. One-sided play.} 12. g3 $1 {Black should never forget that in the Philidor, he is the one who has less space and tries to avoid one-sided playe} O-O-O 13. Qe3 (13. g4 $5 Nhf4 14. h5 Nxe2+ 15. Nxe2 Nf8) 13... Kb8 14. Bh3 Bxh3 15. Rxh3 Qd7 16. Rhh1 Ne7 17. g4 $1 Nf6 18. Kb1 Ng6 19. Ng3 Nf4 ({The only chance in such situations is active, dynamic play.} 19... h5 $5 20. g5 Ng8 {[%csl Gf3][%cal Gf7f6,Gg6h4,Gf8f3]} 21. Nf5 f6 $16) 20. Nce2 Nxe2 21. Qxe2 g6 {[%cal Gh6h5,Gg4g5,Gf6h7,Gf7f6]} 22. h5 $1 {[%csl Gd5][%cal Gd1d3,Gd3b3,Gb3a3,Gc2c4,Gc4c5]} Ng8 23. Qe3 g5 $2 {Positional failiure.} (23... Rf8 24. Rc1 $16) 24. Rd3 Ne7 25. c4 Rc8 26. c5 dxc5 27. Qxc5 Qd6 28. Rc1 (28. Qb5 $1 Qb6 29. Qa4 {[%cal Gh1c1,Gd3b3] would be even stronger.}) 28... Qxc5 29. Rxc5 Rhd8 30. Nf1 Rd7 31. Ne3 f6 32. Rcc3 Rcd8 33. Kc2 Nc8 (33... c6 $1 34. dxc6 Nxc6 (34... Rxd3 35. c7+ Kc8 {[%csl Gd3][%cal Gc2d3,Gc3d3] cxd8+}) 35. Rxd7 Rxd7 36. Nd5 Rd6) 34. Nc4 Nd6 35. Na5 $1 Ka8 36. a4 Kb8 37. b4 Rf8 38. b5 Rg7 39. Nb3 b6 {[%csl Ge6,Gb6,Rc6][%cal Ge7e6]} 40. Rc6 Kb7 41. Rdc3 Ra8 42. Nd2 $1 Rd8 43. Nf1 Re7 44. Ne3 Rf7 45. Kb3 Rdd7 46. Kb4 Rd8 47. a5 (47. Rxd6 $3 Rxd6 48. Nf5 Rh7 49. Rc6 $1 Rxc6 50. dxc6+ Kc8 51. Kc4 {[%csl Rh6,Rf6][%cal Bc4d5,Bd5e6,Rf5h6]}) 47... Kb8 48. Ra3 Kb7 49. Rc1 Rff8 50. Rc6 Rf7 51. Rac3 Kb8 52. Rc1 Kb7 53. R6c3 Re7 54. Rc6 Rf7 55. R1c2 Kb8 56. Rc1 Kb7 57. a6+ Kb8 58. Rxd6 $1 Rxd6 59. Nf5 Rh7 (59... Rd8 60. Nxh6 Rh7 61. Nf5 Rf8 62. Rc6) 60. Rc6 Rxc6 61. bxc6 Kc8 62. Ne3 Kd8 63. Nc4 Ke7 64. Na3 Rh8 65. Nb5 Rc8 66. Kc4 Kd8 67. d6 $1 cxd6 68. Kd5 {[%csl Gf6]} Ke7 69. Nxa7 Ra8 70. c7 Kd7 71. c8=Q+ Rxc8 72. Nxc8 Kxc8 73. Kc6 {1-0 White wins.} 1-0

