{ In the following lecture, you will find some direct attempts to refute the Philidors. They are not very dangerous but Black should know what to do. } 1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. g4 { Is a very dangerous gambit line. It is called "Shirov" line. I suggest two ways of handling the position. } ( 5. Bc4 Be7 6. Bxf7+ $5 { This move was tried many times in practice. At first, it looks dangerous, but actually Black is even better here. Just follow the analyses and you will be OK. } ) 5... Nxg4 { Is of course the most popular and logical move. Black is totally OK, but you must study the position carefully. } ( 5... d5 $5 { Is a very interesting sideline tried less than 100 times. I believe that this move gives Black enough possibilities for Black to keep the game balanced and even to fight for more } ) *
