1. e4 {In this file we will check the immediate tries for the refutation of the Philidor, the sharp lines when White intends to capitalize on the hypothetical weakness of the f7-pawn.} d6 ({In other openings, like the Italian Black has better ways to support his f7-pawn, e.g.} 1... e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 (3... Be7 {[%cal Gf3g5,Ge7g5]}) 4. Ng5 {[%csl Gf7,Gd5,Gc4][%cal Gg5f7,Gd7d5]} d5 5. exd5 Na5) 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. Bc4 {[%csl Rf7][%cal Gc4f7]} Be7 {[%csl Rd8,Ge7][%cal Ge8g8]} (5... c6 $2 6. dxe5 Nxe5 7. Nxe5 dxe5 8. Bxf7+) 6. Ng5 (6. Bxf7+ Kxf7 7. Ng5+ {[%csl Re6][%cal Rf7f8,Rg5e6,Rf7e8]} Kg8 $1 {The correct square.} 8. Ne6 Qe8 9. Nxc7 Qg6 {Technically speaking, White is winning material. In reality, they fell badly behind in the development, and this led to Black's decisive attack.} 10. Nxa8 $2 {this practically loses.} (10. O-O Rb8 11. f4 (11. Qe2 {[%csl Gh6][%cal Ge2e4,Gh7h6]} Nb6 (11... h6) 12. dxe5 dxe5 13. Be3 h6) 11... Nxe4 {[%cal Gc3d5,Gc7d5] Now, depending on which knight will jump on d5, Black must carefully choose his retreat.} (11... h6 12. f5 Qf7 13. d5 (13. Ne6 exd4) 13... Bd8 14. Ne6 Bb6+) 12. N7d5 (12. N3d5 Bd8 $1 (12... Bf8 $2 13. fxe5 dxe5 14. Rxf8+ $1 Kxf8 15. Qf3+ Ndf6 16. dxe5 $16) 13. f5 Qf7 14. Ne6 Bb6 $17 (14... Nb6 $17)) 12... Bf8 $1 (12... Bd8 $2 13. Nxe4 Qxe4 14. dxe5 dxe5 15. fxe5 $13 {[%cal Gb3g8]}) 13. fxe5 Nxc3 14. Qf3 h6 15. Qxc3 dxe5 16. Rxf8+ Kxf8 17. Qa3+ Kf7 18. Qf3+ Nf6 19. dxe5 Qh5 $19 (19... Bg4 $1 20. Qf2 Qf5)) 10... Qxg2 11. Rf1 (11. Ke2 {[%cal Gg4d1]} exd4 12. Rg1 (12. Qxd4 {[%csl Gc8][%cal Gg2h1,Gd4c4,Gc4c8]} Ne5 $19 {[%cal Gc8g4]}) 12... Qxh2 13. Qxd4 Ne5 14. Rg3 (14. Be3 Be6 15. Raf1 Nf3 $3 16. Kxf3 Qh5+ 17. Kf4 Qh4+ 18. Kf3 Bg4+ 19. Rxg4 Qxg4#) 14... Nh5 15. Rf3 (15. Qd5+ Kf8) 15... h6 16. Nd5 Bg4 17. Nxe7+ Kh7 $19) 11... exd4 12. Qxd4 (12. Qe2 dxc3 13. Qc4+ d5 $1 14. Qxc8+ (14. exd5 Kf7 $1 {[%cal Gh8d8]} 15. d6+ Nd5 16. dxe7 Ne5 {[%csl Ge5,Gd5]}) 14... Kf7 15. Qxc3 (15. Qxh8 Qxe4+ 16. Kd1 Qf3+ (16... Qd4+ 17. Ke2) 17. Ke1 cxb2 18. Bxb2 Bb4+ 19. c3 Ne5 $1 20. cxb4 Nd3+ 21. Kd2 Ne4+ 22. Kc2 Qe2+ 23. Kb3 Qxb2+ 24. Ka4 Qxb4#) 15... Qxe4+ 16. Kd1 Rxa8 $19) 12... Ne5 13. f4 $2 (13. f3 Bh3 (13... Nfg4) (13... Nh5 $17 14. Rf2 (14. Qd5+ Kf8) 14... Qg1+ 15. Ke2 h6)) 13... Nfg4 14. Qd5+ (14. Ne2 Bh4+ 15. Ng3 Nxh2 16. Qd5+ Nf7 $19) 14... Nf7 15. Qc4 (15. Qb5 Bh4+ 16. Kd1 Bd7 17. Qe2 Nf2+ 18. Rxf2 Bxf2 $19) 15... Bh4+ 16. Kd1 Be6 $1 (16... Bd7 $1 17. Qe2 (17. h3 Nh2 18. Qe2 Qxf1+ 19. Qxf1 Nxf1) 17... Nf2+ 18. Rxf2 (18. Kd2 Bg4) 18... Bxf2 19. f5 Qg1+ 20. Kd2 Ne5 $19)) (6. dxe5 dxe5 (6... Nxe5 7. Nxe5 dxe5 8. Qxd8+ Bxd8 9. f3 (9. Bg5 c6 10. O-O-O Be7 11. f3 Nd7) (9. Be3 c6 10. a4 Ng4 (10... Bb6 $10) 11. Bc5 Bb6 12. Bxb6 axb6 $10) 9... c6 $10 10. a4 Ba5 11. Ke2 Nd7 $5 12. Be3 Nf8 {[%csl Gd4,Gf4]} 13. Na2 Be6 14. Bd3 Nd7 15. b4 Bb6) 7. O-O (7. Bxf7+ Kxf7 8. Ng5+ {[%cal Gf7g8]} Kg6 $1 9. f4 (9. h4 h5 {The inclusion of these moves favors Black.} (9... h6 10. h5+ Nxh5 11. Qxh5+ Kf6 12. Qf7#) 10. f4 exf4 11. Ne6 (11. Ne2 Bd6 12. e5 Nxe5 13. Nxf4+ Kh6 14. Nf7+ Nxf7 15. Ne6+ Kh7 16. Qd3+ g6 17. Nxd8 Rxd8 $19) 11... Qg8 12. Nxc7 Nc5 $3 (12... Rb8) 13. Nxa8 Bg4 14. Qd4 Qxa8 15. O-O Qd8 16. Qxd8 Rxd8 $19) (9. Ne6 Qg8 10. f4 (10. Nxc7 Rb8 11. N3d5 Nxd5 12. Nxd5 Qd8 $15) 10... h6 $1 11. Nxc7 Rb8 $1 (11... Nc5 $6 12. f5+ (12. O-O Bg4)) 12. N3d5 Bd8 $17) 9... exf4 10. Ne6 Qg8 11. Nxf4+ (11. Nd5 Bd6 12. Nexc7 Bxc7 13. Ne7+ Kf7 14. Nxg8 Rxg8 {[%csl Gf6,Gd7,Gc7]} 15. Qd3 Nc5 16. Qc4+ Ne6 17. O-O g5 $15) (11. Nxc7 Ne5 $1 12. Nxa8 Bg4 13. Qd4 Nc6 14. Qa4 (14. Qf2 Qc4 $1) 14... Bb4 15. O-O Qc4 16. Bxf4 (16. Nc7 Bc5+ 17. Kh1 Qxf1#) 16... Rxa8 $17) 11... Kf7 12. O-O Qd8 13. Nd3 Nc5 $1 14. e5 (14. Ne5+ Ke8) 14... Qd4+ 15. Kh1 Nxd3 16. exf6 Nf2+ 17. Rxf2 Qxf2 18. fxe7 Bg4 19. Qd5+ Be6 20. Qh5+ Kxe7 21. Bg5+ Kf8 $17) (7. Ng5 {[%cal Gd4e5,Gd6e5]} O-O 8. Bxf7+ Rxf7 9. Ne6 Qe8 10. Nxc7 Qd8 11. Nxa8 b5) (7. Qe2) 7... O-O 8. Qe2 (8. Bg5 c6 9. a4 Qc7 10. Qe2 Nc5 11. Rad1 Be6 12. Bxe6 Nxe6 13. Qc4 Rfd8 $10) 8... c6 9. a4 (9. Bg5) 9... Qc7 10. h3 (10. Nh4 Nc5 11. Nf5 Bxf5 12. exf5 Rad8 (12... Rfd8)) (10. a5 Bb4 11. Ng5 b5 12. axb6 Nxb6 $13) 10... Nc5 11. Rd1 Ne6 $10) 6... O-O 7. Bxf7+ (7. f4 c6 {[%cal Gd8a5]} 8. dxe5 dxe5 9. O-O h6 10. Nxf7 Rxf7 11. Bxf7+ Kxf7 12. fxe5 Nxe5 13. Qh5+ Kg8 {[%csl Ge5]} 14. Qxe5 Bd6 $19 {[%csl Re5]}) (7. Be3 Nb6 8. Be2 exd4 9. Qxd4 Ng4 $15 {gaining the bishop pair.}) 7... Rxf7 8. Ne6 Qe8 9. Nxc7 Qd8 10. Nxa8 b5 $1 11. dxe5 (11. a3 Ba6 (11... Bb7)) (11. Nxb5 $2 Qa5+ 12. Nc3 Nxe4 13. O-O Nxc3 14. bxc3 Bb7 15. Qg4 Bf8 (15... Nf6 16. Qe6 Bxa8 $17)) (11. O-O Bb7 12. Nxb5 Bxa8 13. f3 (13. d5 Nxe4 14. Nxa7 Qc7 $15) 13... Qb6 14. a4 a6 15. Nc3 (15. Na3 d5 (15... exd4 16. Nc4 Qc7 17. Qxd4 $4 d5)) 15... exd4 16. a5 Qa7 17. Na4 d5 $17) (11. f3 $5 {Crafty move.} Ba6 $1 {[%cal Gb5b4,Ga6f1]} (11... Bb7 $2 12. Nxb5 Bxa8 (12... Qa5+ $5 {but perhaps dynamic play is OK with} 13. Nc3 d5 $1) 13. d5 $16 {[%csl Gd5,Ge4,Gf3,Gg2]}) 12. dxe5 {A concession.} (12. a4 b4 13. Nb5 Qxa8 14. Nc7 (14. d5 Qb8 15. Be3 Nc5 $15) 14... Qc6 15. Nxa6 Qxa6 $10) 12... Nxe5 $1 13. Nd5 (13. f4 Qxa8 $3 14. fxe5 Nxe4 {[%cal Ge4f2]} 15. Nxe4 Bh4+ $1 16. Ng3 Qxg2 $19) 13... Nxd5 14. Qxd5 Bh4+ 15. Kd1 Bb7 16. Qxb5 Bc6 (16... d5 $1 {[%csl Rd1]}) 17. Qb3 d5 $1 {with decisive attack.}) 11... Nxe5 $1 12. O-O (12. f4 $6 Bg4 13. Qd2 Nc4 14. Qd3 Qxa8 $17 15. Nxb5 Nxe4 16. Qxc4 Nd2 $3 {[%cal Ga8g2,Ge7h4,Gh4e1]} 17. Kxd2 (17. Bxd2 Qxg2 {[%cal Ge7h4,Gg2h1]} 18. Rf1 Bh4+) 17... Qxg2+ 18. Kc3 d5 $1) (12. Bf4 Bd7 $1 13. Qd4 Qxa8 14. Bg3 Bc6 15. f3 Nfd7 $15 (15... a5 $17)) (12. Nd5 Nxd5 13. Qxd5 Qd7 14. O-O Bb7 15. Qd4 Bxa8 $17 16. f4 $2 Bd8) (12. Nxb5 Qa5+ 13. Nc3 Nxe4 14. Qd5 Nc5 $17) 12... Bd7 (12... Bb7 13. Nxb5 Bxa8 14. f3 d5 $1 15. exd5 Bc5+ 16. Kh1 Nxd5 17. Nc3 Bb6 $13) 13. f4 Ng6 14. f5 Ne5 15. Bg5 Bc6 16. Qd4 Qxa8 {[%csl Gb5,Re4]} 17. Rad1 Nc4 18. Rb1 Bd8 {[%cal Gd8b6]} 19. Qd3 Bb6+ 20. Kh1 Nxe4 21. Nxe4 Bxe4 22. Qh3 h6 23. Bc1 Bxc2 24. Ra1 Qe4 25. Bxh6 gxh6 26. f6 Kh7 27. Rf3 Ne5 28. Rg3 Nd3 2