1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. g4 $5 Nxg4 6. Rg1 Ngf6 7. Bc4 { Ng5 } 7... h6 { By far Black's main line. } ( 7... exd4 { By taking on d4 Black solves the problem of protecting the pawn on e5. On the downside, White's development is accelerated, and the centre opens, so Black should be careful about his king's safety. } 8. Qxd4 $5 Nb6 ( 8... c6 9. Bf4 Qb6 $5 ( 9... Nc5 $2 10. e5 $18 { 1-0 (18) Salimova,N (2416) -Strikovic,A (2503) Belgrade SRB 2019 } ) ( 9... b5 10. Ng5 $1 d5 ( 10... bxc4 11. Qxc4 Qe7 12. Qxc6 Rb8 13. O-O-O $18 ) 11. exd5 ( 11. Nxd5 $5 ) 11... Bc5 12. Qd2 bxc4 13. O-O-O cxd5 14. Rge1+ Kf8 15. Nxd5 $18 ) 10. O-O-O ( 10. Qd2 $5 Nc5 ( 10... Qb4 11. Bb3 Nc5 ( 11... Nxe4 $6 12. Qe2 $16 ) 12. Nd4 $13 ) 11. O-O-O Be6 12. Bxe6 Nxe6 13. Ng5 $14 ) 10... Qxd4 11. Rxd4 Nb6 12. Be2 d5 $13 { 1-0 (22) Martinez,A (2209) -Strikovic,A (2493) Forni di Sopra ITA 2018 } ) 9. Bb3 ( 9. Bg5 Nxc4 10. Qxc4 c6 11. O-O-O $44 { Lintchevski-Lorscheid, Tsexia 2006 } ) ( 9. Be2 $5 { Be3,0-0-0 } ) 9... c5 ( 9... Be6 10. Bxe6 fxe6 11. a4 $44 ) 10. Qd3 $44 { 1-0, 21) Krzyzanowski,M (2457) -Szpar,M (2367) Katowice POL 2017 } ) ( 7... Nb6 { [#] } 8. Bxf7+ $1 ( 8. Bb3 $13 { 1-0 Fier,A (2581) -Likavsky,T (2498) /Beijing CHN 2008/The Week in Chess 728 (58) } ) 8... Kxf7 9. dxe5 { As the following variations clearly show it, White has a very dangerous attack. } 9... Ne8 ( 9... Ng4 10. e6+ $1 Kg8 11. Rxg4 Bxe6 12. Rg3 $14 ) ( 9... Nfd7 10. Bg5 $1 ( 10. Ng5+ Kg8 ( 10... Ke7 $2 11. Nd5+ $1 Nxd5 { [#] } 12. Ne6 $18 Kxe6 ( 12... Qe8 13. Qxd5 { Bg5 } ) 13. Qxd5+ Ke7 14. Bg5+ Nf6 15. exf6+ gxf6 16. Bxf6+ ) 11. Nd5 $44 ) ( 10. Nd5 { Bg5 } 10... Nxd5 11. Qxd5+ ( 11. e6+ Kxe6 12. Qxd5+ Ke7 13. Ng5 Ne5 14. f4 c6 15. Qb3 Qb6 $1 16. Qxb6 axb6 17. fxe5 dxe5 $15 ) 11... Ke8 12. exd6 cxd6 13. Qh5+ Ke7 ( 13... g6 $2 14. Rxg6 $18 ) 14. Bg5+ Nf6 15. O-O-O $44 { e5 } ) 10... Qe8 11. Nb5 $16 ) 10. Ng5+ Kg8 11. Nd5 $1 dxe5 ( 11... h6 $2 12. Nxb6 $18 ) 12. Qf3 Qd7 ( 12... Nf6 $2 13. Nxf6+ Qxf6 14. Qb