1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. g4 {I do, however like to present you a fresh, original idea, championed by the Turkish GM Sanal, Vahap.} d5 $5 {[%csl Rg4][%cal Rg2g4] At a glance, This looks illogical, simple loss of a tempo in a sharp position. But as it is often the case, everything can be explained as long as one looks at the position without prejudices. Rather than accepting the sacrifice Black prefers to counter-attack in the center. White's idea was to make use of the potential half-open g-file to pressurize the kingside. If the file remains locked, the g2-g4 move might easily backfire, depriving White of a chance to castle on the kingside.} 6. g5 $2 {Mamedyarov's play was plain bad.} ({A better try is} 6. dxe5 Nxe4 {When both captures have been tested} 7. Nxd5 ({Black is also doing fine after} 7. Qxd5 $5 Nxc3 8. bxc3 c6 9. Qd4 ({Or} 9. Qd3 Qa5 (9... Bc5 10. Bf4 Qe7 $44) 10. Bf4 $2 (10. e6 $1 fxe6 11. Qe3 $14 (11. Bg2 Be7 12. Bd2 O-O 13. O-O Qc7 14. Ng5 Bxg5 15. Bxg5 {1/2-1/2 (15) Deutschbein,C (2006) -Hermannsdoerfer,F (2188) Berlin 2016}) 11... Nf6 12. Bd2 Nxg4 (12... Bc5 $1 13. Qf4 O-O {is more convincing.}) 13. Qe2 Nf6 14. Bh3 Qd5 ({Here best was} 14... Be7 $1 15. Bxe6 Bxe6 16. Qxe6 Qd5 17. Qxd5 Nxd5 $17) 15. Rd1 Qe4 16. Be3 e5 17. Bg2 Bg4 18. h3 Bh5 19. O-O Bc5 20. Rfe1 Bxe3 21. Qxe3 Qxe3 22. Rxe3 e4 $17 {Weetik,V (2423) -Koellner,R (2454) Chess. com INT 2022}) 10... Nc5 11. Qe3 Bxg4 $17 {and Black was in full control in Costachi,M (2463) -Koellner,R (2440) Chess.com INT 2022. Koellner is another notable name for the whole line.}) 9... Qb6 ({Correct was} 9... Bc5 $1 10. Qe4 Qe7 $44 {as} 11. Bg5 {is met with} f6) 10. Bc4 Nc5 11. Be3 (11. Ng5 $16 {[%csl Rf7]}) 11... Ne6 12. Qe4 Bc5 13. Nd4 Nxd4 14. Bxd4 Bxd4 15. Qxd4 Qa5 16. O-O-O O-O 17. f4 $2 (17. Kb1 $14) 17... Be6 (17... Bxg4 18. Rdg1 Rad8 $17) 18. Bxe6 fxe6 19. Qc4 Kh8 20. Rhf1 Rae8 21. Kb1 Rd8 22. Rd4 Rd5 23. Rxd5 cxd5 24. Qb4 Qd8 25. f5 Rf7 26. Rf4 h6 27. Kb2 a5 28. Qd4 Qd7 29. a4 exf5 30. gxf5 Rxf5 31. Rxf5 Qxf5 32. Qxd5 Kh7 33. Qd6 Qf4 34. e6 Qxd6 {0-1 (34) Corrales Jimenez, F (2532) -Shahinyan,D (2456) Lichess.org INT 2020}) ({Noone tried yet} 7. e6 fxe6 8. Nxe4 dxe4 9. Ng5 Qe7 10. Nxe4 Qb4+ 11. Nc3 Bc5 $13 {but Black seems good here too}) 7... Nb6 $1 {[%csl Gd1,Gf2][%cal Ge4f2,Gd8d1]} (7... c6 8. Ne3 Qa5+ 9. Bd2 Qc7 (9... Nxd2 10. Qxd2 Qxd2+ 11. Kxd2 Bc5 $44) 10. Nf5 Nxd2 (10... Nxe5 $17 11. Qe2 Nxf3+ 12. Qxf3 Nxd2) 11. Qxd2 Nxe5 12. Qe3 Bxf5 13. gxf5 Bd6 $10 {Black does not have any problems at all.} 14. Nxe5 O-O-O (14... Qa5+ $14 15. c3 Qxe5) 15. f4 f6 16. Qxa7 Bxe5 17. fxe5 (17. Bc4 $1) 17... Qxe5+ 18. Be2 Rhe8 $19 {Remizov,Y (2428) -Sanal,V (2563) Chess.com INT 2021}) 8. c4 (8. Nxb6 Qxd1+ 9. Kxd1 axb6 10. Ke2 Bxg4 11. Ke3 Nc5 $15) 8... c6 9. Ne3 $6 (9. Nxb6 Qxd1+ 10. Kxd1 axb6 11. Ke2 Bxg4) 9... Qxd1+ 10. Nxd1 Bxg4 11. Be2 Bb4+ $19 12. Kf1 O-O-O (12... Bh3+ 13. Kg1 O-O-O) 13. Kg2 Nd2 14. a3 Nxf3 15. Bxf3 Bxf3+ 16. Kxf3 Bd2 17. Rg1 g6 18. c5 Nc4 19. Ke4 Rd5 20. f4 Rhd8 21. b3 Na5 22. Bxd2 Rxd2 23. Rb1 R2d3 24. e6 f6 {0-1 (24) Salinas Herrera, P (2513) -Koellner, R (2432) Chess.com INT 2021}) ({The acid test for the whole line is} 6. exd5 e4 {and now not} 7. Ne5 $6 ({But} 7. g5 {[%cal Ge5e4] which is logically the only way to justify White's play. Then after} exf3 8. gxf6 Nxf6 9. Qxf3 {Black may try various things, but my preferred idea is} Qe7+ (9... Bd6) (9... Bb4 $5) (9... Bg4) 10. Be3 (10. Qe3 Bf5) 10... Bg4 11. Qg2 (11. Bb5+ $2 c6) 11... O-O-O 12. Be2 $6 Bxe2 13. Nxe2 Qb4+ {and nothing is clear at all.}) 7... Bb4 $1 {Black has no problems whatsoever.} 8. Bd2 (8. Bc4 Nb6 ({Simple and good is} 8... O-O {with the idea} 9. g5 Nxe5 10. dxe5 Bg4 11. Qd4 c5 12. Qe3 Nxd5 $13) 9. Bb5+ Kf8 (9... Nfd7 $11) 10. Bd2 Bd6 $2 11. Bg5 h6 12. Bh4 g5 13. Bg3 Nbxd5 14. Nxd5 Nxd5 15. Qe2 $14 {Bykhovsky,A (2496) -Koellner,R (2337) Chess.com INT 2020}) (8. Bg5 h6 (8... O-O $11) 9. Bxf6 Nxf6 10. Bb5+ c6 $5 11. dxc6 O-O 12. Qd2 e3 $3 {[%csl Rh1][%cal Rd8d5,Rd5b5,Rd5h1] A key tactical idea in all these lines worth remembering!} 13. Qxe3 Bxc3+ 14. Qxc3 Qd5 {[%csl Rb5,Rh1][%cal Rd5b5,Rd5h1]} 15. O-O-O Qxb5 16. Rhg1 Ne4 17. Qe3 f6 18. c4 Qa6 19. Qxe4 fxe5 20. dxe5 Qxc6 21. Qxc6 bxc6 22. f4 Rxf4 23. Rd8+ Rf8 24. Rgd1 Bxg4 {0-1 (24) Wieczorek, O (2407) -Jobava,B (2705) Warsaw 2013}) 8... O-O {This might be even better!} ({Than} 8... Bxc3 9. bxc3 Nxe5 10. dxe5 Bxg4 11. Be2 (11. Bb5+ c6 12. dxc6 Bxd1 13. c7+ Qd7 14. Bxd7+ Nxd7 15. Rxd1 Rc8 $10 16. Rg1 (16. Bf4 Nc5 $10) 16... Rxc7 17. Rxg7 Nxe5 $10) 11... Bxe2 12. Qxe2 Nxd5 13. Qxe4 Qd7 $15 14. O-O-O Qe6 (14... O-O-O $1 15. Bg5 f6 16. exf6 gxf6 17. Bxf6 $2 (17. Bh4 Nxc3 (17... Qd6 $5) 18. Rxd7 Nxe4 19. Re7 f5) 17... Nxf6) 15. Rhg1 g6 16. c4 Nb6 17. Bh6 Rd8 18. Bg7 Rg8 19. Bf6 Rxd1+ 20. Rxd1 Nd7 21. Qxb7 Nxf6 22. exf6 Qxf6 23. Qc8+ Ke7 24. Rd7+ Ke6 25. Qxc7 Kf5 26. Rd5+ Kg4 27. Qg3# {1-0 (27) Zubov,A (2598) -Koellner, R (2441) Chess.com INT 2021}) 9. Be2 (9. Rg1 Bxc3 10. bxc3 Nxd5 $15) 9... Nxe5 ({Jobava's idea can be used with a different, but equally cruel intention in the line} 9... Re8 $5 {[%csl Re1]} 10. Nxd7 Bxd7 11. g5 e3 $3 12. fxe3 (12. Bxe3 Nxd5 13. Bd2 Bxc3 14. bxc3 Bg4 $19) 12... Bxc3 13. bxc3 (13. Bxc3 Nxd5) 13... Nxd5 $19) 10. dxe5 Bxc3 11. Bxc3 Nxd5 12. Qd4 c5 $6 (12... Nxc3 13. Qxc3 Be6 14. Rd1 (14. Qe3 Qd5) 14... Qe7 15. O-O (15. Qe3 Qb4+) 15... Qg5 $40) 13. Qxe4 Nxc3 14. bxc3 Bd7 15. Bd3 g6 16. O-O Bc6 $44 {Roganovic,M (2490) -Tadic,B (2563) Belgrade 2015}) (6. Nxd5 Nxd5 (6... exd4) 7. exd5 e4 8. Qe2 (8. Nd2 e3 (8... Nf6) 9. fxe3 (9. Ne4 exf2+ 10. Nxf2 Be7 $36 {[%cal Ge8g8,Gf8e8,Ge7h4,Ge7b4]}) 9... Qh4+ 10. Ke2 Nf6 $17 {[%csl Gg4][%cal Gc8g4]}) (8. Ne5 Bd6 9. Nc4 Nf6 $10) 8... Nf6 (8... Be7 $1 9. Qxe4 Nf6 10. Qd3 Bxg4 $44) 9. g5 Nxd5 10. Qxe4+ Be7 11. Bd3 (11. c4 $16) 11... Nb4 12. Bd2 Nxd3+ 13. Qxd3 Qd5 $44 {Salimova,N (2399) -Sanal,V (2601) Chess.com INT 2022}) 6... Nxe4 7. Nxd5 (7. Nxe4 dxe4 8. Nxe5 Nxe5 9. dxe5 Qxd1+ 10. Kxd1 Bc5 $17) 7... c6 8. Nc3 (8. Ne3 Nxg5 9. Nxe5 Nxe5 10. dxe5 Qa5+ 11. Bd2 Qxe5 12. Qe2 Be6 13. Bc3 Qf4 14. O-O-O Ne4 15. Be1 Bc5 16. Rg1 O-O 17. Kb1 Rad8 18. Rc1 Qxh2 19. Rg2 Qf4 20. Ng4 Rfe8 21. f3 Bxa2+ 22. Kxa2 Nc3+ 23. Bxc3 Rxe2 24. Bxe2 Qxc1 25. Nf6+ Kf8 26. Nxh7+ Ke7 27. Bc4 Kd7 28. Bxf7 Kc8 29. Be5 Bd6 30. Bc3 Qf4 31. Rxg7 Be5 32. Be6+ Kb8 33. Rg4 Qh2 34. Ba5 Bc7 35. Bxc7+ Qxc7 36. Ng5 Qa5+ 37. Kb3 Qb5+ 38. Ka2 Qa5+ 39. Kb3 Qb5+ 40. Ka2 a6 41. b3 Rd2 42. Kb2 Qe5+ 43. Kc1 Qe1+ 44. Kb2 Qe5+ 45. Kc1 Re2 {0-1 (45) Siva,M (2349) -Sanal,V (2581) Chess.com INT 2020}) 8... Qa5 ({Black alreday had a pleasant choice.} 8... Nxc3 9. bxc3 Bd6 $15) 9. Bd2 Nxd2 10. Qxd2 Bb4 $15 11. dxe5 O-O ({Even better might have been} 11... Nb6 $1 12. Rd1 Nd5 13. Bc4 Nxc3 14. a3 Nxd1 15. axb4 Qc7 16. Qxd1 Bg4 $19) 12. O-O-O Nb6 13. Qe3 Bg4 14. Bd3 Bh5 15. Nb1 Bc5 16. Qe4 Bg6 17. Qe2 Qxa2 18. c3 Nd5 19. Bxg6 fxg6 20. Nd4 Rae8 21. Rhe1 Rf4 22. b4 Qxb1+ {0-1 Black wins.} 0-1

