1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. Bc4 Be7 6. O-O O-O 7. a4 c6 8. Re1 a5 9. b3 { [%csl Rc4] Another useful move. Compared to the previous line, the white bishop remains flexible. } 9... Nb6 { I find this to be the most accurate move order, which practically wins a tempo for Black. } ( { The main line however remains } 9... exd4 10. Nxd4 { [%csl Rc4] } ( { In case of } 10. Qxd4 { we can use a familiar tactic } 10... Ne5 $1 { to level the chances, say } 11. Nxe5 ( 11. Be2 { [%cal Ge5f3] } 11... Nfg4 12. h3 Nxf3+ 13. Bxf3 Ne5 14. Be2 f5 $13 { [%cal Gd6d5] } ) 11... dxe5 { White should definitely avoid } 12. Qxe5 $6 { [%csl Rh6][%cal Ge7d6,Rh7h6] } 12... Ng4 { [%csl Re5] } 13. Qf4 ( 13. Qg3 $4 Bh4 { [%csl Rf2] } ) 13... Bd6 { [%csl Rh2][%cal Rd8h4] } 14. e5 Nxe5 $17 15. Rxe5 $2 Qc7 $19 { [%csl Re5] } ) 10... Nb6 11. Bd3 { This is the difference in comparison to the immediate Nd7-b6. } ( { Instead } 11. Bf1 { [%csl Gf1,Gd3] } 11... d5 { may transpose into the game after } 12. e5 Ne8 ( { But Black also has an additional idea } 12... Ne4 $5 13. Nxe4 dxe4 14. Bb2 ( 14. c3 f5 15. exf6 Bxf6 16. Ba3 Re8 $13 ) ( 14. Rxe4 $4 c5 ) 14... f5 15. exf6 Bxf6 16. Rb1 ( 16. c3 Bxd4 17. Qxd4 Qxd4 18. cxd4 Bf5 19. Rac1 Rfe8 20. Ba3 Nd5 { should be holdable. } ) 16... Re8 17. g3 Nd5 18. Bg2 e3 19. Bxd5+ ( 19. f4 $2 Nb4 $19 ( 19... Kh8 20. Qh5 Re7 21. Rbd1 Qe8 22. Qxe8+ Rxe8 23. Bxd5 cxd5 24. Rd3 e2 25. Bc3 { 1-0 (55) Quesada Perez,Y (2478) -Maiwald, J (2543) Havana 2004 } ) ) 19... Qxd5 20. fxe3 Bh3 { more than enough compensation for the pawn. } ( 20... Bg5 21. Qd3 ) ) 13. Bd3 ( 13. Nce2 $5 g6 { [%csl Gf1] } ) ) 11... d5 12. e5 { [%csl Rd3,Rf1] } 12... Ne8 { [%cal Gc1d2,Gc1b2,Gc3e2,Ge2g3,Gg3f5,Gd1f3,Gg4h5] The critical position for the line. Black's plan includes g7-g6, Ne8-g7 to protect on the kingside, Nb6-d7-c5, and ideally f7-f6. The positions are dangerous for the second player, but they are playable. See the continuations below: } 13. Qh5 ( 13. Qf3 g6 14. Bh6 Ng7 { [%cal Re7g5] } 15. Rad1 Bg5 ( 15... Bb4 $5 { [%csl Rd3] } 16. Bf1 ( 16. Nde2 { [%csl Re5] } 16... Re8 ) 16... Nd7 { [%cal Rd7c5,Rd8c7,Rd7e5,Gd8h4,Rh4h6,Rh4d4] } ) 16. Bxg7 Kxg7 17. Nce2 Bh6 18. Nf4 Qg5 $13 { Jansa,V (2449) -Neuman,P (2497) Czech Republic 2013 } ) ( 13. Bd2 g6 14. Nce2 Ng7 15. Nf4 c5 $6 ( 15... Nd7 $1 16. e6 Nc5 { [%cal Gg7e6,Gc5e6,Gc8e6] } 17. exf7+ Rxf7 ) 16. Nb5 Be6 17. Nxe6 fxe6 18. Qg4 ( 18. Rf1 $5 ) 18... c4 19. Bf1 cxb3 20. cxb3 Bc5 21. Be3 Nd7 22. Qh3 Bxe3 23. Qxe3 Nf5 24. Qh3 Nc5 25. Bd3 Nh4 26. Bc2 Qe7 27. Qe3 { 1/2-1/2 (27) Kindermann,S (2536) -Maiwald,J (2514) Austria 2005 } ) ( 13. Nce2 { [%cal Gc3e2] } 13... g6 14. Bh6 ( 14. c3 Ng7 15. Nf4 Nd7 16. Bc2 Qc7 17. Nd3 f6 $13 { [%csl Rd4,Rc3,Rd3][%cal Rc2d3] Cao,S (2492) -Nguyen,H (2311) Ho Chi Minh City 2013 } ) ( 14. Ng3 Ng7 15. c3 f6 $2 ( 15... Nd7 $1 { [%cal Rd7c5,Rc5e6] } ) 16. exf6 ( 16. e6 $1 { [%csl Rb6][%cal Rb6c5] } 16... c5 { [%csl Rg3] } 17. Ndf5 $3 gxf5 18. Nxf5 Nxf5 ( 18... Nxe6 19. Rxe6 $1 { [%cal Rd1g4,Rg4g7] } ) 19. Bxf5 $18 { [%csl Rh7][%cal Gd1h5,Gh5h7,Rd1g4,Rc1h6] } ) 16... Bxf6 17. Ba3 Rf7 18. Qc2 $14 { Studer,N (2422) -Menezes, C (2364) Khanty-Mansiysk 2015 } ) 14... Ng7 15. Qd2 $5 Re8 ( 15... Nd7 { [%csl Gf5,Ge6][%cal Gd7c5,Gc5d3,Gc8f5] } ) 16. c3 c5 17. Nb5 { [%csl Rb5] } 17... Nf5 18. Bf4 Be6 19. Bxf5 $1 Bxf5 20. e6 $18 { Vovk,Y (2539) -Stojanovic,A (2318) Cappelle la Grande 2011 } ) ( 13. Bb2 { [%cal Gc1b2] } 13... g6 14. Kh1 Ng7 15. f4 Bc5 $6 ( 15... Nd7 $13 ) 16. Nce2 Bg4 17. Qd2 Nc8 18. f5 $18 ) 13... g6 14. Qh6 Ng7 { [%csl Gb6,Rd3][%cal Gf7f6,Gb6d7,Gd7c5] } 15. Nce2 Re8 16. Ng3 Bf8 { [%csl Rh6] } 17. Bg5 Qc7 18. Qh4 Rxe5 19. Bd8 Rxe1+ 20. Rxe1 Qd6 $44 { Felgaer,R (2593) -Strikovic,A (2465) Santa Cruz de La Palma 2005 } ) 10. Be2 ( 10. Bd3 { [%cal Ge5d4,Gd6d5] } 10... Bg4 { [%csl Gd4][%cal Ge5d4] } ( 10... Re8 { [%csl Gd4,Rd3][%cal Gf8e8,Gd4e5,Gd6e5,Gf3e5] } 11. h3 Qc7 12. Bb2 Bf8 13. Qd2 Bd7 14. Rad1 exd4 15. Nxd4 d5 16. exd5 Nbxd5 17. Nxd5 Nxd5 18. Bc4 Rxe1+ 19. Rxe1 { 1/2-1/2 (19) Malisauskas,V (2516) -Koziak, V (2470) Police 2010 } ) 11. Be2 ( 11. dxe5 dxe5 12. h3 Be6 { [%cal Rf3e5,Rd8d4] } ( 12... Bxf3 13. Qxf3 Bb4 14. Bb2 Nfd7 15. Red1 Re8 16. g3 Re6 { [%cal Rf6f2] } 17. Bf1 Rf6 18. Qh5 Qe7 19. Bg2 Qc5 { Favarel,A (2240) -Rogozenco,D (2557) Naujac 2011 } ) 13. Bb2 Nfd7 14. Ne2 f6 $15 { [%csl Rg7,Rf6,Re5,Rb2][%cal Rg7b2] Manhardt,T (2234) -Jovanovic,Z (2505) Austria 2016 } ) ( 11. Be3 Nfd7 12. Be2 Re8 13. h3 Bxf3 14. Bxf3 Bg5 15. g3 Bxe3 16. fxe3 Nf6 $17 { Lanka,Z (2510) -Bezold, M (2534) Austria 2006 } ) 11... Nbd7 12. h3 Bh5 13. Be3 Re8 14. Nd2 Bxe2 { Vuckovic,B (2623) -Markus,R (2616) Vrnjacka Banja 2010 } ) 10... exd4 11. Nxd4 d5 12. e5 Ne8 13. Bd3 { [%csl Rd3][%cal Rc4e2,Re2f1,Rf1d3] } 13... g6 { [%csl Rb4,Rc5,Rd4,Rc3][%cal Ge8g7,Rf2f4,Re7c5,Rc5b4,Rb4e1] With an extra tempo, Black's chances are definitely improved and they can hope for gradual improvement, equalization and can even think for more than an equality later. } ( { An additional resource is the immediate } 13... Nd7 $5 14. e6 ( 14. f4 g6 15. f5 ( 15. Nce2 Nc5 16. Ng3 f6 ( 16... f5 ) ) ( 15. Kh1 Bb4 ( 15... Nc5 16. f5 ) 16. Bb2 ( 16. Bd2 Nc5 17. Nce2 ) ( 16. Nce2 Bxe1 17. Qxe1 Nc5 ) 16... Nc5 17. f5 Qh4 $13 ( 17... Nxd3 18. Qxd3 Qg5 $13 ) ) ) 14... Nc5 ) 14. Nf3 ( 14. Bh6 Ng7 15. Nce2 Nd7 ( 15... Re8 { [%cal Gb6d7,Gd7c5] } 16. Ng3 Bg5 17. Bxg7 ( 17. Bxg5 Qxg5 18. Nf3 Qf4 19. Ne2 Qh6 20. Ned4 Bg4 21. Qd2 Qxd2 22. Nxd2 Rad8 ( 22... Ne6 ) 23. f3 Bc8 24. f4 Nd7 $1 25. N2f3 Nc5 { Testor,S (2365) -Jovanovic,Z (2520) Austria 2011 } ) 17... Kxg7 18. f4 Bxf4 19. Nh5+ gxh5 20. Qxh5 Qg5 21. Qxh7+ Kf8 $19 { Tomic,B (2409) -Jovanovic,Z (2577) Zupanja 2011 } ) 16. f4 ( 16. Nf4 { [%csl Gf4][%cal Ge2f4] } 16... Nc5 17. e6 $6 fxe6 18. Bxg6 hxg6 19. Nxg6 Rf6 $19 { Mulet,P (2284) -Malaniuk,V (2496) Zabrze 2011 } ) 16... Nc5 17. f5 { [%csl Rd3] } 17... Nxd3 18. Qxd3 Bxf5 ( 18... Nxf5 $1 19. Bxf8 Bxf8 $44 { [%csl Gd5] } ) 19. Nxf5 Nxf5 20. Bxf8 Bxf8 21. Nf4 Bg7 22. Re2 Qb6+ 23. Kh1 Q